cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with diffusion on complex networks and the decision power of agents in strategic diffusion. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational aspects of finding the optimal sequence of nodes to activate a network in minimum time, and presents an algorithm based on dynamic programming. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper treats diffusion as a strategic problem and analyzes the possibility of developing an efficient approximation algorithm. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with decision-making by agents in strategic diffusion. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper proves that finding an optimal solution to the problem is NP-complete in a general case, and analyzes the approximation guarantee of heuristic algorithms.
